<!-- ════ QUICK SUMMARY ════ -->
<section id="at-glance" class="section section--place" style="background:#F8F4EC;padding:var(--section-pad)">
 <div class="container">
  <div class="summary-callout">
   <h2>At a Glance</h2>
   <p>Vision 2040 treats parks and recreation as economic development infrastructure. Tournament-grade athletic facilities generate sports tourism revenue, support school programs, and keep youth sports dollars from flowing to competing cities. Community parks and trails create the everyday quality-of-life that attracts families and supports housing values.</p>

   <div class="summary-grid">
    <div class="summary-item">
     <h4>⚽ Athletic Complex Initiatives</h4>
     <ul>
      <li>Renovated athletic complex with tournament-grade turf fields</li>
      <li>Capability to host regional and state tournaments</li>
      <li>10,000 sq ft indoor multi-use facility for year-round programming</li>
      <li>400-seat bleacher capacity</li>
      <li>Drainage and irrigation for all-weather use</li>
      <li>Natural grass option for soccer, lacrosse, field hockey</li>
      <li>Est. $4.5M investment</li>
     </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="summary-item">
     <h4>⛳ Golf Club Renovation</h4>
     <ul>
      <li>Championship-standard course upgrade</li>
      <li>Modernized clubhouse with pro shop, restaurant</li>
      <li>Driving range and short-game practice area</li>
      <li>Annual El Dorado Open (200+ players)</li>
      <li>KGCA-sanctioned tournament hosting</li>
      <li>Public & private membership tiers</li>
      <li>Est. $2.2M investment</li>
     </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="summary-item">
     <h4>🏊 Aquatic & Recreation Centers</h4>
     <ul>
      <li>Renovated public swimming pool (Olympic dimensions)</li>
      <li>Splash pad for young children</li>
      <li>Indoor recreation center (15,000 sq ft)</li>
      <li>Climbing wall, basketball, volleyball, ping-pong</li>
      <li>Community meeting & event space</li>
      <li>Year-round programming</li>
      <li>Est. $3.2M investment</li>
     </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="summary-item">
     <h4>📍 Park System Improvements</h4>
     <ul>
      <li>Linear parks along Walnut River</li>
      <li>North Gateway Linear Park (5 miles, paved trail)</li>
      <li>26-mile Lake Circumnavigation Trail</li>
      <li>Accessible playground (ADA-compliant)</li>
      <li>Dog park (2 acres, fenced)</li>
      <li>Disc golf course (18-hole)</li>
      <li>Picnic shelters, restrooms, parking</li>
     </ul>
    </div>
   </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ════ DATA SOURCES ════ -->
  <div class="data-sources-box">
   <h3>📚 Data Sources</h3>
   <p>This page incorporates data from the following sources:</p>
   <ul class="sources-list">
    <li><strong>DataUSA:</strong> <em>El Dorado, KS profile</em> — Age demographics (youth population), household composition. <a href="https://datausa.io/profile/geo/el-dorado-ks/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">datausa.io/profile/geo/el-dorado-ks/</a></li>
    <li><strong>Kansas Health Matters:</strong> <em>Physical Activity & Recreation Indicators</em> — Community recreation participation rates, health outcomes related to physical activity. <a href="https://www.kansashealthmatters.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">kansashealthmatters.org</a></li>
    <li><strong>NRPA (National Recreation & Parks Association):</strong> Parks ROI, sports tourism benchmarking, facility utilization studies</li>
    <li><strong>Kansas Youth Sports Commission:</strong> Tournament hosting capacity data, sports tourism economic impact models</li>
    <li><strong>El Dorado School District (USD 490):</strong> Youth sports participation data, facility utilization patterns</li>
   </ul>
  </div>
 </div>
</section>

<!-- ════ MAIN CONTENT ════ -->
<section id="content-section" class="section section--place" style="padding:var(--section-pad)">
 <div class="container">

  <h2 style="margin-bottom:2rem">Major Parks & Recreation Projects</h2>

  <div id="athletic-complex" class="glass-card reveal">
   <span class="badge badge--navy">Athletic Development · $4.5M</span>
   <div class="icon">⚽</div>
   <h3>Renovated Athletic Complex — Tournament-Grade Facilities</h3>
   <p>The existing El Dorado athletic complex is undersized and lacks the infrastructure to host regional and state-level tournaments. Vision 2040 calls for a complete renovation:</p>
   <ul style="margin-top:1rem;margin-left:1.5rem">
    <li>Expand from 4 to 6 tournament-grade turf fields</li>
    <li>All-weather drainage and irrigation</li>
    <li>10,000 sq ft indoor multi-use facility for year-round programming</li>
    <li>400-seat bleacher capacity</li>
    <li>Dedicated parking for 200+ vehicles</li>
    <li>Concession facilities and spectator amenities</li>
   </ul>
   <p style="margin-top:1rem"><strong>Sports Tourism Impact:</strong> Regional tournaments (youth soccer, lacrosse, field hockey) bring 100–500 visiting families per weekend, generating $30K–$100K in direct economic activity per tournament. 6–8 tournaments per year = $200K–$600K annual tourism revenue.</p>
  </div>

  <div id="golf-club" class="glass-card reveal">
   <span class="badge" style="background:#8b7a5a">Golf Destination · $2.2M</span>
   <div class="icon">⛳</div>
   <h3>El Dorado Golf Club — Championship Renovation</h3>
   <p>The existing golf club is an underutilized asset with potential for significant upgrade. Championship-standard renovation includes:</p>
   <ul style="margin-top:1rem;margin-left:1.5rem">
    <li>Full course redesign (18 holes, par 71–72)</li>
    <li>Modernized clubhouse with pro shop, restaurant, event space</li>
    <li>Driving range expansion and short-game practice area</li>
    <li>Cart paths, irrigation, and bunker renovation</li>
    <li>Improved accessibility for golfers with disabilities</li>
   </ul>
   <p style="margin-top:1rem"><strong>Revenue Model:</strong> Public play rates ($35–$55 per round), membership tier options, annual El Dorado Open (200+ players, $15K–$25K in tournament entry fees), corporate outings, and league play. Conservative estimate: $300K–$400K annual revenue; reinvested in maintenance and programming.</p>
  </div>

  <div id="aquatic-center" class="glass-card reveal">
   <span class="badge" style="background:#2c5aa0">Aquatic & Recreation · $3.2M</span>
   <div class="icon">🏊</div>
   <h3>Aquatic Center & Indoor Recreation Facility</h3>
   <p>Vision 2040 modernizes El Dorado's water recreation and year-round community facility options:</p>
   <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:1.5rem;margin-top:1.5rem">
    <div>
     <h4>Aquatic Center</h4>
     <ul>
      <li>Renovated Olympic-size pool (50m x 25m)</li>
      <li>Shallow splash pad (young children)</li>
      <li>Zero-entry recreation pool (ADA accessible)</li>
      <li>Seasonal operation (May–August)</li>
      <li>Learn-to-swim programs (600+ youth annually)</li>
      <li>Summer league competition platform</li>
     </ul>
    </div>
    <div>
     <h4>Indoor Recreation Center</h4>
     <ul>
      <li>15,000 sq ft multi-use facility</li>
      <li>Climbing wall (45 ft)</li>
      <li>2 basketball courts (convert to volleyball)</li>
      <li>Racquetball/squash courts</li>
      <li>Fitness area, game room, meeting space</li>
      <li>Year-round programming (fitness, youth, senior)</li>
     </ul>
    </div>
   </div>
  </div>

  <div id="parks-trails" class="glass-card reveal">
   <span class="badge" style="background:#6b8e23">Park System · $2.8M</span>
   <div class="icon">🌳</div>
   <h3>Parks & Trails System Expansion</h3>
   <p><strong>North Gateway Linear Park (Phase 1):</strong> A 5-mile paved multi-use trail connecting Butler CC campus through East Park, Central Park, and North Main Park to the athletic complex. KDOT-funded pedestrian/bike path spine through downtown. Tree canopy expansion, interpretive signage, accessible restrooms at mile-1 intervals.</p>
   <p style="margin-top:1rem"><strong>Community Parks:</strong></p>
   <ul style="margin-left:1.5rem">
    <li>Renovated Central Park (downtown plaza + splash pad for summer)</li>
    <li>Accessible Playground (all-abilities, ADA-compliant equipment)</li>
    <li>Off-Leash Dog Park (2 acres, fenced, waste stations)</li>
    <li>18-Hole Disc Golf Course (free public play, championship-grade)</li>
    <li>Picnic Shelters (reservation system for community events)</li>
    <li>Restroom Facilities (seasonal, ADA-accessible)</li>
   </ul>
  </div>

  <div id="accessibility" class="glass-card reveal">
   <span class="badge" style="background:#c44536">Accessibility Initiative · Ongoing</span>
   <div class="icon">♿</div>
   <h3>ADA Accessibility & Inclusive Recreation</h3>
   <p>Every Vision 2040 parks and recreation project incorporates full ADA compliance and inclusive design principles:</p>
   <ul style="margin-top:1rem;margin-left:1.5rem">
    <li>All trails: 5-ft minimum width, <5% slope</li>
    <li>Parking: 1 accessible space per 25 spaces (minimum)</li>
    <li>Restrooms: ADA-compliant at all facilities</li>
    <li>Playgrounds: Universally-designed equipment (ages 2–12, all abilities)</li>
    <li>Water Access: Zero-entry pools and dock fishing access</li>
    <li>Signage: Large print + Braille at all facilities</li>
    <li>Programming: Adaptive recreation programs (youth & adult)</li>
   </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- ════ SPORTS TOURISM MATH ════ -->
  <h2 style="margin-top:3rem;margin-bottom:2rem">Sports Tourism Economics</h2>

  <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,.05);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.2);border-radius:var(--radius);padding:2rem">
   <h3>Tournament Revenue Model</h3>
   <p>A single regional youth soccer tournament (100–150 teams, 200–400 families, 2-day event):</p>
   <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:1.5rem;margin-top:1.5rem">
    <div>
     <strong>Per-Family Spending</strong>
     <ul>
      <li>Hotel: 2 nights @ $100/nt = $200</li>
      <li>Meals: $80 (breakfast, lunch, dinner)</li>
      <li>Retail: $40 (gas, ice cream, souvenirs)</li>
      <li style="border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.2);padding-top:.75rem;margin-top:.75rem"><strong>Total: $320/family</strong></li>
     </ul>
    </div>
    <div>
     <strong>Per-Tournament Total</strong>
     <ul>
      <li>300 families × $320 = $96K</li>
      <li>Tournament entry fees: $4,500 (split w/city)</li>
      <li>Concessions (city/vendor split): $2,000</li>
      <li>Parking revenue: $1,000</li>
      <li style="border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.2);padding-top:.75rem;margin-top:.75rem"><strong>Total: ~$100K impact</strong></li>
     </ul>
    </div>
    <div>
     <strong>Annual Tournament Schedule</strong>
     <ul>
      <li>Spring soccer (Feb–Apr): 3 tournaments</li>
      <li>Summer lacrosse (May–Jul): 2 tournaments</li>
      <li>Fall field hockey (Aug–Oct): 2 tournaments</li>
      <li>Winter basketball (Dec–Feb): 1 tournament</li>
      <li style="border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.2);padding-top:.75rem;margin-top:.75rem"><strong>Total: 8 tournaments/yr</strong></li>
      <li><strong>Annual Impact: ~$800K</strong></li>
     </ul>
    </div>
   </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ════ COMMUNITY IMPACT ════ -->
  <h2 style="margin-top:3rem;margin-bottom:2rem">Community Benefits</h2>

  <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:1.5rem">
   <div style="background:rgba(107,142,35,.1);border:1px solid rgba(107,142,35,.3);border-radius:var(--radius);padding:1.5rem">
    <h4>Youth Development</h4>
    <ul>
     <li>600+ youth in swim programs annually</li>
     <li>1,000+ youth in organized sports</li>
     <li>Lower obesity rates (active recreation)</li>
     <li>Improved school attendance & academic performance</li>
     <li>Reduced juvenile crime (structured activity)</li>
     <li>Skill-building & team development</li>
    </ul>
   </div>
   <div style="background:rgba(74,144,191,.1);border:1px solid rgba(74,144,191,.3);border-radius:var(--radius);padding:1.5rem">
    <h4>Adult & Senior Programs</h4>
    <ul>
     <li>Fitness classes & recreation leagues</li>
     <li>Golf club & tennis programs</li>
     <li>Senior walking groups & activities</li>
     <li>Improved health outcomes (physical activity)</li>
     <li>Community social connection</li>
     <li>Active aging initiatives</li>
    </ul>
   </div>
  </div>

 </div>
</section>

